\documentclass{article}

\begin{document}
\SweaveOpts{concordance=TRUE}

\title{sgRNA-Level LFC, SE, and Z-Score Analysis}
\maketitle

\section{Overview}

This analysis calculates LFC (log fold change), SE (standard error), and Z-scores 
using batch-regressed and normalized data. This is the \textbf{secondary analysis} 
(sgRNA-level) for robustness validation, consistent with Zhu et al. 2025 methodology.

\textbf{Method:}
\begin{enumerate}
  \item For each sgRNA: compute mean and variance across all cells with that sgRNA
  \item Compute mean and variance across all NTC cells (global baseline)
  \item LFC = sgRNA mean - NTC mean
  \item SE = sqrt(var\_sgRNA/n\_sgRNA + var\_NTC/n\_NTC)
  \item Z-score = LFC / SE
  \item P-values from Welch's t-test (two-sided)
\end{enumerate}

The Good News - Self-Targeted Validation is Strong
